hu.trigary.iodine.api.gui

Interface DrawPrioritizeable<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the class implementing this interface
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ButtonGuiElement, CheckboxGuiElement, ContinuousSliderGuiElement, DiscreteSliderGuiElement, DropdownGuiElement, GridGuiContainer, GuiContainer<T>, GuiElement<T>, IodineOverlay, LinearGuiContainer, ProgressBarGuiElement, RadioButtonGuiElement, RectangleGuiElement, TextFieldGuiElement, TextGuiElement, TextureGuiElement

    public interface DrawPrioritizeable<T>
    Represents something that can be drawn in an environment where overlapping might happen.

    The draw priority number determines whether this instance should be rendered behind or in front of other instances. The instance with the highest value is drawn on top of all other instances. The number must be at least Byte.MIN_VALUE and at most Byte.MAX_VALUE.

    By default elements are drawn in the order they are added, so the default draw priority is an internal incrementing counter.

    Changing the draw priority of a GuiContainer causes all of its child GuiElements to update their priority: the child's draw priority is set to the container's draw priority if its previous value is less than this new value.
